entries.femaleVariant: It's V. Heard you had a gig for me.
You heard right. I need a driver.
Listen, I'm a straight-shooter, so lemme cut right to the chase.
You say you've heard of me... can't say the same for you. Lots of question marks above this job.
entries.maleVariant: You say you've heard of me... can't say the same for you. Lot of question marks above this job.

entries.femaleVariant: I don't like cabs. They have a bad habit of bolting when things gets dicey.
Oh, y'know, this an' that. I got a few errands to run, couple friends that need payin' a visit. The usual.
I heard you're the best in town. Thing is, I like workin' with the best, and I know the best don't come cheap.
I'm not gonna get into the nuts and bolts, 'cause if what they say about you is true, you can handle anything.
So let's get this settled. You got what it takes, or are they wrong about you?
Yeah... Call me if you change your mind.
Well, we doin' this or not?
Japantown, then. By the market entrance. Give a few honks and I'll stroll up. Later, V.
